description:
Our people love the exciting and meaningful work they do, the cutting-edge resources and technology they have access to, the benefits we offer and the great community we’ve built. Want to join them?As a Trainee Data Analyst in Kainos, you will be responsible for matching the needs of data insight with understanding of the available data. Data analysts work closely with customers to produce insight products including reports, dashboards and visualisations but also contribute to project understanding of existing data structures so that inputs and outputs are fully understood.
We are seeking more high calibre people to join our Data & Analytics capability where you will grow and contribute to industry-leading technical expertise. Requirements:
• Currentlystudying, or already completed, a relevantdegree or equivalentqualification;
• Fluency in English (at least B2 level)
• Experience of discovering, gathering and wrangling data from various data sources for analysis ;
• Ability to... understand the client’s business challenge and work with colleagues to identify data visualisation and dashboard approaches to help address the customer needs;
• Understanding how to identify missed opportunities for data insight;
• Basic understanding of data model and modelling techniques;
• Clear written and verbal communication skills; ability to explain findings and techniques to a non-technical audience;
• Awareness for the importance of stakeholder engagement and understands how to gather data requirements;
• Familiarity with the production of data analysis outputs such as profiling reports, data quality reports, etc.;
• Good SQL knowledge; able to read and understand XML and JSON;
• Ability to advise managers on the estimated effort and technical implications of data insight products;
• Ability to prioritise and work to deadlines;
• Ability to work collaboratively with others.
Desirable:
• Experienced with structured and unstructured data
• Ability to review and comment on data models– for example pointing out why models are defective and suggesting improvements.
• Ability to give feedback and mentor more junior colleagues
• Experience of Power BI, Tableau and
• Experience of Google Analytics (other web analytics tools)
• Experience in combining qualitative and quantitative datasets
• Experience of system performance analysis.

​
Assessments (an online interview and an online group exercise) are likely to take place in April 2023.
These roles will commence in Summer 2023 – one Academy starting in June and the other in August.
Please note that this is a hybrid opportunity, which means that you may be required to work from our Gdansk office at least 3 times a week. Please remember to attach your CV in English.At Kainos, we recognise many of the greatest ideas and innovations come from a diverse mix of minds, backgrounds and experiences, and are committed to cultivating an inclusive working environment that drives changes in Technology. Therefore, we particularly welcome applications from groups who are typically under-represented in this sector including women, non-binary and transgender people. Read about flexible working, parental leave and other benefits . All appointments will be on the basis of merit. WHO YOU ARE:Our vision is to enable outstanding people to create digital solutions that have a positive impact on people’s lives. Our values aren't abstract; they are the behaviours we expect from each other every day and underpin everything that we do. We expect everyone to display our values by being determined in how obstacles are overcome; honest when dealing with others; respectful of how you treat others; creative to find solutions to complex problems and cooperative by sharing information, knowledge and experience. These values, applied collectively, help to produce an outstanding Kainos person, team and culture
